summary: One person accepting you can make all the difference.  I just wanna put it out there that this is not a phan drawing. This is...
caption:
One person accepting you can make all the difference. 

I just wanna put it out there that this is not a phan drawing. This is not an indication of their romantic relationship. This is a bond, whether it be romantic or not. 

Phil was the first person to truly and fully accept Dan for who he is. He showed Dan there is nothing “wrong’ with his sexuality. He showed him that there was nothing to be afraid of. He guided him into the light. And that’s what I wanted to show here. They are no longer in the dark. They are heading towards something so much bigger and better - acceptance. Love. Encouragement. And happiness. So much happiness. 

I am so proud of you @danielhowell and @amazingphil. I have looked up to you since I was maybe 12 - 8 years later and I am so honored to see how you’ve grown. I can’t wait to see what doors open now. 

Also thank you to my fiancee @singyoutosleep for helping me brainstorm this idea lmao. We met through Dan and Phil, so this means the absolute world to us.

summary: I'm a socially anxious person, my whole life I've been trying to blend in and not get the attention of others so I wore mainly...
body:
I’m a socially anxious person, my whole life I’ve been trying to blend in and not get the attention of others so I wore mainly black, dark blue and grey (I still do), but a month before my graduation prom, Dan and Phil (who I’ve been watching on YouTube for a while) went to the British Online Creator Awards as disco balls and I thought “It’s the end of school and I really want to go all out” and that’s when I bought 2 shiney dresses and dyed my hair bright pink, because that’s something I never had the courage to do and I would never have done it if it weren’t for them.

Dan and Phil had helped me a lot through tough times, but after watching them going this bright to a big social event, that was when they made me stand up for myself, for myself. I’ll never forget it, because to this day these dresses are my favorite dresses of all time and I NEVER wear dresses.

Thank you Dan and Phil for showing me that no one actually cares how you dress as long as you feel comfortable. That’s still something I have to learn, but you helped me with the first steps.
